<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy — 0xdpslabs" description="Privacy policy for 0xdpslabs and associated projects">
  <h1>Privacy Policy — 0xdps labs</h1>
  <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary); font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);">Last Updated: December 2025</p>

  <h2>Introduction</h2>
  <p>
    0xDPS is an independent developer ecosystem that creates tools, extensions, APIs, and utilities for software developers. 
    This Privacy Policy explains our general data-handling principles and links to the individual policies for each product.
  </p>
  <p>
    By using any 0xDPS product, you agree to the individual privacy policy for that product and this general policy.
  </p>

  <h2>What Information We Collect (General)</h2>
  <p>
    Across the ecosystem, we may collect limited data solely for functional or analytical purposes, depending on the product. 
    This may include:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Basic technical data (IP, device info, logs)</li>
    <li>Error logs or crash reports</li>
    <li>Authentication-related identifiers (if applicable)</li>
    <li>Data required for using APIs or extensions</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <strong>We do not sell, trade, or share personal data with third parties.</strong> Each product declares its own specific behavior.
  </p>

  <h2>What We Do Not Collect</h2>
  <p>Unless explicitly required:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>We do not collect personal identity information</li>
    <li>We do not track users across websites</li>
    <li>We do not store private content, code, or messages</li>
    <li>We do not monetize or analyze user data</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Products Covered</h2>
  <p>Each product has its own privacy policy:</p>
  
  <div style="margin-top: var(--spacing-md); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);">
    <div class="project">
      <h3 class="project__name"><a href="/privacy/pingpong">PingPong</a></h3>
      <p class="project__description">Browser extension for API testing</p>
    </div>
    <div class="project">
      <h3 class="project__name"><a href="/privacy/mockly">Mockly</a></h3>
      <p class="project__description">Mock API service for developers</p>
    </div>
    <div class="project">
      <h3 class="project__name"><a href="/privacy/folioport">FolioPort</a></h3>
      <p class="project__description">Static portfolio generator</p>
    </div>
    <div class="project">
      <h3 class="project__name"><a href="/privacy/gitplus">GitPlus</a></h3>
      <p class="project__description">VS Code extension for Git workflows</p>
    </div>
    <div class="project">
      <h3 class="project__name"><a href="/privacy/pinboard-gpt">Pinboard GPT</a></h3>
      <p class="project__description">Browser extension for ChatGPT message pinning</p>
    </div>
    <div class="project">
      <h3 class="project__name"><a href="/privacy/sheetalchemy">SheetAlchemy</a></h3>
      <p class="project__description">Python library for Google Sheets</p>
    </div>
    <div class="project">
      <h3 class="project__name"><a href="/privacy/devops">Azure DevOps Org</a></h3>
      <p class="project__description">0xDPS organization policy</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Data Security</h2>
  <p>All tools follow standard security practices:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>HTTPS/TLS encryption</li>
    <li>No unnecessary data retention</li>
    <li>Least-privilege access within infrastructure</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Infrastructure providers include:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Microsoft Azure</li>
    <li>Vercel</li>
    <li>Fly.io</li>
    <li>GitHub</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>User Rights</h2>
  <p>You may request:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Information about data stored</li>
    <li>Deletion of any personal data associated</li>
    <li>Revocation of access</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For privacy inquiries or requests, contact us at:<br />
    <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:dps.manit@gmail.com">dps.manit@gmail.com</a>
  </p>

  <h2>Updates</h2>
  <p>
    This policy may change as our ecosystem evolves. Updates are reflected on this page with the "Last Updated" date.
  </p>

  <footer class="footer">
    <p><a href="/">← Back to home</a></p>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>
